<paragraph blockId="14.[138,259,1580,1604]" box="[138,259,1580,1604]" pageId="14" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis box="[138,259,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="177">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[138,1185,1628,1685]" lastBlockId="15.[125,1172,137,323]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="178" pageId="14" pageNumber="177">
Length of fore wing: 
<emphasis box="[389,407,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="177">„</emphasis>
<quantity box="[416,503,1629,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount box="[518,532,1628,1653]" pageId="14" pageNumber="177" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[541,672,1629,1653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="177" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 mm</quantity>
. Frons brown, terminal half of palpus grey, third segment of female palpus of medium length. Antenna lamellate in both sexes. Abdominal crests with metallic glossy sheen. Wing shape as in previous species, with colour more grey or greyish brown, irrorated with many more dark blackish scales. Markings on both wings and both upper- and underside same as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Holloway" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1996" box="[832,1113,201,225]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[832,984,201,225]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">M. variegata</emphasis>
Holloway
</taxonomicName>
, but subterminal lines missing; discal spot, although of same shape as in that species, much weaker on upperside; underside much darker, purplish grey, subterminal band rather indistinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[125,1172,395,484]" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[125,292,395,419]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Very similar to previous species, differing only in having the apical part of the valva narrower, the central basal lobe of the valva somewhat quadrate and the blade-like saccular process slightly broader.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[125,1172,557,613]" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[125,307,557,581]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[325,444,557,581]" captionStart="Figures 69–74" captionStartId="23.[125,194,1320,1339]" captionTargetBox="[175,1117,143,1274]" captionTargetId="figure-125@23.[170,1127,133,1284]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Figures 69–74. Female genitalia. (69) M. opalina (IZCAS Geom-00103). (70) M. albescens (IZCAS Geom- 00030). (71) M. purpurivenata sp. nov., holotype (IZCAS Geom-00109). (72) M. subradiata (BMNH Geom- 20968). (73) M. medullosa (ZFMK 2740). (74) M. cineracea (BMNH). Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214626/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">Figure 74</figureCitation>
). Very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Inoue. Ductus" authorityName="Inoue. Ductus" box="[765,1086,557,581]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis box="[765,905,557,581]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">M. albescens</emphasis>
Inoue. Ductus
</taxonomicName>
bursae somewhat thinner and shorter, corpus bursae a little bigger.
</paragraph>
