<paragraph blockId="15.[125,220,962,986]" box="[125,220,962,986]" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis box="[125,220,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[125,1172,1011,1132]" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">
It is possible that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1996" box="[367,517,1011,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cineracea">
<emphasis box="[367,517,1011,1035]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">M. cineracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1996" box="[594,747,1011,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Metallolophia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[594,747,1011,1035]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">M. variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent seasonal forms or ecologically separated forms of the same species, judging from the similarity of the genitalia, size and pattern, but more collecting, particularly in the areas between the locations where the 
<typeStatus box="[171,220,1108,1132]" pageId="15" pageNumber="178">type</typeStatus>
material originates, would be necessary to establish this.
</paragraph>
